Coastal
The following figure shows the average price of electricity in the Coastal region for each customer class and year. Between 2011 and 2019, the region experienced decreasing prices for Commercial and Other customers, while Residential customers have seen a slight increase in price.
The average real price (in 2021 dollars) of electricity for Residential customers in the Coastal region rose 6% from $0.17/kWh in 2011 to $0.18/kWh in 2019. The average price of electricity for Commercial customers in the Coastal region fell 5% from $0.21/kWh in 2011 to $0.20/kWh in 2019. Finally, the average price of electricity for Other customers in the Coastal region fell 15% from $0.40/kWh in 2011 to $0.34/kWh in 2019. Residential customers in the Coastal region saw increases in electricity while commercial and other customers saw decreases. However, the residential customer class continues to pay the lowest per kWh in the region due to a combination of low prices in high population areas and PCE subsidies in eligible communities.

